MY MEME

This is very appropriate and well described what I feel right now, so I thought it would be interesting to make a MEME about it!

meme

library(magick)
#Add text content with a new blank image
dog_text <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Life before \ntaking Stats220...",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 40,
                 font = "Helvetica", 
                 gravity = "center")

#Get image from a web page
dog <- image_read("https://thehappypuppysite.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Cute-Dog-Names-HP-long-1024x555.jpg") %>% 
  image_resize("500x500!")

#Complete 1st part
top_row <- image_append(c(dog, dog_text))

#Add text content with a new blank image
cat_text <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "After taking \nit!", 
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 40, 
                 font = "Helvetica", 
                 gravity = "center")

#Get image from a web page
cat <- image_read("https://i.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/original/000/026/489/crying.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("500x500!")

#Complete 2nd part
bottom_row <- image_append(c(cat, cat_text)) 

#Combine 2 layers
meme <- image_append(c(top_row,bottom_row), stack = TRUE) %>% image_scale(500)

#Save the meme as a new png file
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")
MY GIF

This is a moment!

animation

library(magick)
#Extract 4 images that I need
frame1 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Life before \ntaking Stats220...",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 40,
                 font = "Helvetica", 
                 gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame2 <- image_read("https://thehappypuppysite.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Cute-Dog-Names-HP-long-1024x555.jpg") %>% 
  image_resize("500x500!")

frame3 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "After taking \nit!", 
                 color = "#FFFFFF", 
                 size = 40, 
                 font = "Helvetica", 
                 gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame4 <- image_read("https://i.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/original/000/026/489/crying.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("500x500!")

#Create an animation GIF
#Create frames by combining all image frames 
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)
animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 2) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "DS student's life", color = "#FF8000", size = 30, gravity = "south")
image_morph(animation)

# save and name this GIF
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
